3 (b) Membership.
4 (1) The Recreational Trails Compensation Study Committee shall be
5 composed of the following members:
6 (A) the Commissioner of Forests, Parks and Recreation or designee;
7 (B) the Commissioner of Taxes or designee;
8 (C) a representative of the Vermont Trails and Greenways Council,
9 appointed by the Governor;
10 (D) a representative of the Vermont Outdoor Recreation Economic
11 Collaborative, appointed by the Speaker of the House;
12 (E) a representative of a land conservation organization, appointed by
13 the Committee on Committees;
14 (F) a private landowner who has a conservation easement that
15 includes recreation, appointed by the Governor;
16 (G) a private landowner who does not have a conservation easement
17 on the land and currently provides public access, appointed by the Speaker of
18 the House;
19 (H) a representative who has expertise in trail planning, design,
20 building, and maintenance, appointed by the Committee on Committees; and
