5 (c) Powers and duties. The Recreational Trails Compensation Study
6 Committee shall:
7 (1) review how private property currently is made available for use by
8 public recreational trails;
9 (2) summarize the costs and liabilities that private property owners incur
10 when private property is used by public recreational trails;
11 (3) assess available economic data and other relevant available data or
12 analysis and conduct further necessary economic analysis to determine the
13 value that recreational trail access provides to the State and to local economies;
14 (4) investigate whether and how private property owners in other
15 jurisdictions are compensated for allowing use of property for public
16 recreational trails or other public outdoor recreation;
17 (5) recommend to the General Assembly whether real property owners
18 who allow use of their property for public recreational trails should receive
19 compensation or other benefit and, if so, the source of the compensation or
20 other benefit;
