6 (d) Assistance. The Recreational Trails Compensation Study Committee
7 shall have the administrative, technical, and legal assistance of the Department
8 of Forests, Parks and Recreation.
9 (e) Report. On or before December 15, 2026, the Recreational Trails
10 Compensation Study Committee shall submit a written report to the General
11 Assembly with its findings and any recommendations for legislative action.
12 (f) Meetings.
13 (1) The Commissioner of Forests, Parks and Recreation or designee
14 shall call the first meeting of the Recreational Trails Compensation Study
15 Committee to occur on or before September 15, 2025.
16 (2) The Commissioner of Forests, Parks and Recreation or designee
17 shall be the chair of the Study Committee.
18 (3) A majority of the membership shall constitute a quorum.
19 (4) The Committee shall cease to exist on March 1, 2027.
